From 250df8df53573d723705a1b2a8c8903f2ba6910f Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: BeCurious Scheduler <saleh@emergegcc.com>
Date: Mon, 13 Apr 2026 01:20:49 +0300
Subject: [PATCH] feat: data isolation, enhanced import, class field, driver
 dashboard
MIME-Version: 1.0
Content-Type: text/plain; charset=UTF-8
Content-Transfer-Encoding: 8bit

1. Dev/main data isolation: Vercel preview/dev deployments now use a
   separate Supabase row ('dev') so testing never overwrites live data.
   Yellow "DEV" badge shown on non-production deployments.

2. Enhanced spreadsheet import: reads Class, Type (1-on-1/Guest/Host),
   Group Host, Rejected Days columns. New "Replace all" checkbox wipes
   roster and schedule for fresh imports. Lat/Lon now optional (warn only).
   Guests auto-link to host students in the same class.

3. Class field: new "cls" property on students, visible in Students table,
   sortable. groupHost dropdown now respects same-class rule — guests can
   only be assigned to hosts in their class.

4. Driver/cost dashboard: toolbar shows "Drivers" count (cars with ≥1
   session today). New "Drivers / cost" tab in Reports shows drivers
   needed per day, peak count, and which cars are in use — for daily
   rental cost planning.

Patch-0026
